  "title": "An Odd Acquaintance Turns into a Promising Endeavor",
  "summary": "Arriving at the crowded Etti IV spaceport for a weapons-shop auction, the weary smuggler captain Violet 'Allure' nearly collides with Malif Tal-Tahn, a soft-spoken near-human OOAG auditor who is also eyeing the same lot. Discovering they are rival bidders against Colonel Delede rather than partners, the two strike up a cordial acquaintance and retire to the Xanadu club for drinks and a meal, where Violet's connoisseur taste in liquor clashes amusingly with the establishment's cheap fare. Over Cassandra Sunrises and conversation, Malif reveals his interest in securing an off-the-books pipeline for weapons, and offers to back Violet's auction bid as a silent partner. Violet slips him a holo contact device, framing the arrangement as an investment in future business, and departs confident he will take her up on the offer.",
